      h3 What is the mission of IdeaJam?

      p IdeaJam exists to create the greatest engine for innovation that the world has ever known.

      h3 How can I make money or earn rewards on IdeaJam?

      p IdeaJam allows you to mine your inventive thought for rewards.   For example, every action leading to innovative thought on IdeaJam enables you to earn Einstein Points.  Einstein Points are redeemable for Amazon ® Gift Cards.  Thus, when you contribute inventive thought, whether identifying an imperfection of someone else’s idea, suggesting a solution for someone else’s idea, or building out your own invention’s “idea profile,” you can mine rewards.  Moreover, IdeaJam incorporates a crowdfunding feature where you can raise money for your own ideas or support other projects.   When you submit a solution to improve someone else’s idea on IdeaJam, if that user chooses to incorporate your suggestion into a variant of his or her own idea, a percentage of the crowdfunding raise is reserved for you.  The percentage available is determined by the number of suggestions the original inventor incorporates from the IdeaJam crowd.  A baseline of 10% per crowdfunding raise is reserved for submitters of solutions on IdeaJam.  This portion of the crowdfunding raise is then divided equally among the IdeaJam users who have submitted solutions chosen by the original inventor to incorporate into a variant of his or her idea.  In other words, if a crowdfunding campaign were to raise $100,000 and five solutions were chosen by the original inventor into the idea variant underpinning the campaign, each of person who submitted a solution would earn $2,000 as a result of the campaign.  In exchange for earning a portion of the crowdfunding raise, you agree to assign the rights in the improvement to the inventor’s original concept back to the inventor to further invest in and commercially exploit.

      h3 What are “Idea Variants?” 

      p After you have exposed your idea to the IdeaJam crowd, preferably after filing a provisional patent application related to your idea, other members of the crowd can add imperfections and suggest solutions associated with your idea.  You will receive a notification overlaying the notifications icon in the top left area of the IdeaJam interface whenever someone adds an imperfection or solution.  You can create an infinite number of variants of your idea by incorporating others’ solution suggestions into your own concept.  The creation of a variant should not impact your rights in any previously disclosed idea that you already have filed a provisional patent application for patent pending over (though you should discuss this with a patent attorney).   Should you choose to generate a provisional patent application for an idea variant from that variant’s profile, and then subsequently raise money through IdeaJam’s crowdfunding platform for that variant, the submitters of the solutions that you incorporated into the variant will earn 10% of the crowdfunding raise equally divided among them.  For example, if you incorporate five suggested solutions into a variant of your original idea and then crowdfund the variant, each of the people who submitted a suggestion that you accepted would earn 2% of your ultimate crowdfunding raise.  In exchange for providing a percentage of your crowdfunding raise, those submitting suggested solutions agree to assign all patent rights to you for indefinite term, enabling you to freely commercially exploit the variant of your idea.

      h3 What are “Einstein Points”?

      p Every action of special value that you take on IdeaJam, whether upvoting a suggested solution, creating an imperfection, crowdfunding a concept or starting a new idea, has a point reward associated with it.  Einstein Points provide a number of benefits for you on IdeaJam.  First, you can redeem the Einstein Points you earn for Amazon ® Gift Cards at the present per-point reward value.   Second, Einstein points can help validate you as an innovator.  Whenever you identify and articulate the imperfections of someone else’s idea, or more importantly offer solutions to imperfections of ideas on IdeaJam, you earn Einstein Points.  Your Einstein Point value translates to rankings within your networks and among innovative peers.  You can see where you stack up!  Also, Einstein Points are used to rate IdeaJam “Jam” networks against each other.  This enables you to see how your town stacks up with other towns, how your company stacks up with other companies, and how your school stacks up with other schools.

      h3 How can I mine Einstein Points on IdeaJam?

      p IdeaJam rewards your innovative thought contributions.  Every action that you take on IdeaJam in furtherance of innovation will earn you Einstein Points.   Wherever you see the Einstein Point “coin” icon, by taking the related action, you will earn Einstein Points.  Some actions are worth more Einstein Points than others.   As a general rule, when someone else validates your inventive contributions, you will earn more points.  For instance, you will earn a relatively higher number of Einstein Points when someone else upvotes your inventive contribution, or chooses to incorporate a suggestion that you have offered into a variant of their own invention.

      h3 How is the Einstein Points per-point Amazon ® Gift Card reward value calculated?

      p IdeaJam continuously monitors the actual value of the account that houses the rewards funds and divides that value by the total number of unredeemed Einstein Points outstanding on the IdeaJam network.   This represents the per-point value of an Einstein Point.

      h3 How do I redeem Einstein Points for an Amazon ® Gift Card?

