      h3 Why do I need to pay a fee to redeem my Einstein Points?

      p While most of IdeaJam is free, the premium services of IdeaJam do require payment.  A percentage of this payment is transferred to a rewards account to enable the IdeaJam network to redeem their points for a reward.   IdeaJam does require a $20.00 fee to redeem points which goes directly back into the rewards fund.  Why?  Well, simply, if everyone simultaneously made a run on the rewards fund without putting money back into the account, the point value would quickly plummet to zero.  By maintaining a fee to redeem points, we ensure that you only reward points when you have earned a significant amount of points, and we also ensure that the account balance never plummets to zero.   The redemption fee therefore preserves and safeguards the reward value of Einstein Points for all.

      h3 How can I create a patent application on IdeaJam?

